{
  "stem": "10353.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But the way we went to the train-- to the railway station, there were columns of hundreds and hundreds of hundreds emaciated people coming, you know, that could hardly walk, that they were dragging themselves, urged on by the SS with-- with all kinds of beatings.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we were going on one side of the road.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They were on the other side of the road.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "In any event, we were put into the wagons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And we were taken-- the-- the train pulled out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we were traveling we didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We didn't know nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "By that time, the SS that were escorting us were a little bit on the milder side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They were-- they were in a separate wagon, and they let us get out of our wagons to go out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, we came in to a city called Luneburg, something, Luneburg.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And it was immediately after that particular railway station was heavily bombarded by the Allies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And the freight cars were filled with food, with cigarettes, with chocolates, with everything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And we sort of let loose there and we raided that place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And we tried to stuff ourselves with whatever we could.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And we were crawling from one place to another.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I was just crawling under-- under one of the freight cars to go into another freight car when one of the Sonderwaffen-- what they called it-- these were in the black uniforms with a-- shoved a pistol against me.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "He says-- and he didn't shoot, but he yelled in German, [SPEAKING GERMAN]-- this is enough, get back, which we did.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "We were traveling for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] several days, because the train apparently was zig-zagging, trying to get through the Elbe River.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
